annotationA: Uncharacterized protein, isoform A; It is involved in the biological process described with: endosome transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway
annotationB: Vacuolar protein sorting 20 (Vps20) is a member of the ESCRT-III complex, which sorts certain endocytosed receptors for degradation via the multivesicular body. As part of this complex, Vps20 is also involved in abscission following cytokinesis; Belongs to the SNF7 family
